description:
Bible for Kids Bedtime Stories – Offline Audiobook

Bible for Kids Bedtime Stories is an offline audiobook created especially for toddlers, preschoolers, and children of all ages. In the app, you’ll find the most important Bible stories, written in simple, child-friendly language and narrated by a professional voice actor.

The gentle storytelling and calming background music help children understand these ancient sacred stories and relax before bedtime. You can listen to the Bible for Kids offline — at home or on the go, without an internet connection. The app contains no ads and is 100% safe for children.

The Best Bible Stories for Kids

The “Bible for Kids Bedtime Stories” app includes the following Bible stories and parables in audiobook format:

- Creation of the World;
- Expulsion of Adam and Eve;
- Noah and the Great Flood;
- The Tower of Babel;
- God’s Promise to Abraham;
- Jacob and Esau;
- The Story of Joseph;
- The Story of Moses;
- In the Promised Land;
- The Birth of Jesus;
- The Boy Jesus at the Temple;
- The Miraculous Catch of Fish;
- Jesus Feeds 5,000 People;
- The Resurrection of Lazarus;
- Jesus Came to Jerusalem;
- Judas’ Betrayal;
- Taking Jesus into Custody;
- Jesus on the Cross;
- Jesus Is Resurrected!;
- The Road to Emmaus;
- The Prodigal Son;
- Jesus Calms the Storm;
- Jesus Heals a Blind Man;
- The Ascension of Jesus;
- Coming soon;

Benefits of the Bible for Kids Bedtime Stories App:

- Professional voice actor;
- Calm background music;
- 100% kid-safe;
- No ads;

The Bible consists of two parts:

Old Testament
The Old Testament tells the story of how God created the world and the first people — Adam and Eve. This part of the Bible includes many stories from the lives of the ancient Hebrews: how the patriarchs lived in the lands of the Middle East, raising their flocks; how the descendants of Abraham were enslaved in Egypt and later freed by God; how the people made a covenant with the Lord on Mount Sinai and received the Ten Commandments; and how God promised to lead His people to the Promised Land.

New Testament
The New Testament tells the story of the earthly life of Jesus Christ — from His miraculous birth to His crucifixion and glorious Resurrection. In this part of the Bible, you will find stories about Jesus’ ministry, His parables and miracles, the Last Supper, His suffering, death on the cross, and Resurrection. The New Testament also describes the beginnings of the early Christian communities, the deeds of the apostles, and the letters written by Christ’s followers to believers around the world.

The Holy Bible is a collection of diverse texts — myths, legends, prayers, historical narratives, and prophecies. Many biblical stories need explanation for modern children, so our audio Bible retells them in simple and clear language.

Believe in God and Jesus Christ, grow in faith, live with love, and listen to these Bible audio stories together with your children.
